To setup, follow Instructions below:

1. Install basic requirements.
-- git
-- hg
-- pip
-- Google App-Engine Python SDK ( Add to system PATH )

2. Get dependencies.
$ ./get-dependencies.sh

3. Add/Edit application name.
Add/edit the application name at the top of the app.yaml file.

4. Add/Edit required keys and Google project-ID.
Add the following information at the bottom (in the env_variables section) of the apps.yaml file: 
DROPBOX_APP_KEY
DROPBOX_APP_SECRET
GOOGLE_PROJECT_ID
GOOGLE_API_KEY

To run the application locally:
$ python manage.py runserver

To deploy the application to Google App Engine (Follow the next step to complete deployment):
$ python manage.py deploy

To upload the app-template to Amazon S3:
$ pip install boto
$ export AWS_ACCESS_KEY_ID=<Your AWS Access Key ID>
$ export AWS_SECRET_ACCESS_KEY=<Your AWS Secret Access Key>
$ python deploy_S3.py

For more options:
$ python manage.py --help